\mathcal{L}_i(a) = 1 - \frac{\mathcal{L}_i^{\text{lik}}(a)}{1 + \mathcal{L}_i^{\text{lik}}(a)}

where \mathcal{L}_i^{\text{lik}}(a) = \frac{p_i^{\text{human}}(s_i(a))}{p_i^{\text{non-human}}(s_i(a))} and s_i(a) is the sufficient statistic (e.g., n_a, \text{LID}_a, \alpha, \Psi).

